@NODE Introduction
@TITLE "snes9xstarter À Introduction"


    @{b}Introduction@{ub}


    snes9xstarter is a small GUI using MUI for the MorphOS
    port of SNES9X, an emulator for the Super Nintendo
    Entertaiment System.

    The idea bases on snes9xstarter from Pawel 'stefkos'
    Stefanski, but this version 2.0 was written completly
    from scratch.

    

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements
@TITLE "snes9xstarter À Requirements"


    @{b}Requirements@{ub}


    - MorphOS 1.4

    - get9.library 
      ( get ot from http://www.christianrosentretr.com/releases/ )

    - SNES9x (MorphOS port by Fabien Coeurjoly)

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation
@TITLE "snes9xstarter À Installation"


    @{b}Installation@{ub}


    Copy the snes9xstarter drawer to a place you like.
    But best is probably to copy all the files (snes9xstarter,
    logo.png and this guide) simply to the SNES9X directory.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Startup
@TITLE "snes9xstarter À Startup"


    @{b}Startup@{ub}

    
    You can start snes9xstarter from Ambient or from the
    CLI.
 

    @{b}Ambient@{ub}

    No special options or tooltpyes are required. It
    still supports all default MUI- and Commodity-
    tooltypes.



    @{b}CLI@{ub}

    No special options required or supported.

@ENDNODE


@NODE MainWindow
@TITLE "snes9xstarter À Main window"


    @{b}Main window@{ub}


    The main window is divided in 2 pages.

    @{b}General@{ub}

        Quick Selector

            Here you can quickly select a ROM image, so
            you don't need to open the ASL requester.

        ROM

            Here you can alternatively choose a ROM
            Image with an ASL requester.

        Start Emulator

            After you selected a ROM image (either with
            the quick selector or the ASL requester) you
            can start snes9x with the configured settings.


    @{b}Settings@{ub}


        SNES9X Path (required)

            Configure the location of your SNES9X
            executable. When you installed snes9xstarter
            directly into the SNES9x drawer then you
            probably don't need to configure this.

        ROM Path

            Chosse the path where your ROM images are
            located. snes9xstarter will scan this path
            and show all found files in the Quick Selector.

        Filter Pattern

            The patter which is used to filter the right
            files into the Quick Selector.


        Display
        Sound
        Emulation
        Advanced

            Here you can set certain options for SNES9x.
            Please read your SNES9x documentation about
            the certain possible options.

            snes9xstarter comes per default with optimal
            settings for most games. You maybe only need
            to configure the display settings for your
            preference (fullscreen and/or overlay).


        Show Console Output

            When deactivated the SNES9x CON output goes
            to NIL:, else a CON window will open to display
            SNES9x output.



        HINT: Save (prefered) settings permanetly by using
              the "Settings -> Save" menuitem.

@ENDNODE

@NODE MenuOptions
@TITLE "snes9xstarter À Menuoptions"


    @{b}Menu options@{ub}


    @{b}Project@{ub}

        About...

            Opens the About window with copyright information and
            credits.

        About MUI...

            Opens MUIs About window.

        Quit

            Quits snes9xstarter immediatelly.


    @{b}Settings:@{ub}


        Load last saved

            Loads last saved configuration.

        Save

            Saves current settings to disk.

        MUI...

            Opens MUI Settings.

@ENDNODE

